<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" />
  <title>TransitCloud Docs — Index</title>
  <meta name="description" content="TransitCloud documentation index: quickstart, formats, proof bundles, verification, custody/transport, and sandbox packet." />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="./styles.css" />
</head>
<body>
  <header class="topbar">
    <div class="container topbar__inner">
      <a class="brand" href="./index.html">
        <span class="brand__mark" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="brand__name">TransitCloud</span>
        <span class="brand__tag">Docs</span>
      </a>

      <nav class="nav">
        <a href="./index.html">Home</a>
        <a class="is-active" href="./docs.html">Docs</a>
        <a href="./developers.html">Developers</a>
      </nav>

      <div class="topbar__cta">
        <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="./developers.html#api">API</a>
        <button class="iconbtn" id="themeToggle" aria-label="Toggle theme" title="Toggle theme">◐</button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main>
    <section class="pageHead">
      <div class="container">
        <h1>Documentation Index</h1>
        <p class="lead">Everything needed to build, verify, and pilot TransitCloud in regulated workflows.</p>

        <div class="searchRow">
          <input id="docSearch" type="search" placeholder="Search docs (e.g. canonical, ed25519, bundle, custody, anchor)..." />
          <span class="kbd">Ctrl / ⌘ + K</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="docsGrid" id="docsGrid">
          <a class="docCard" href="#quickstart" data-tags="quickstart install cli verify">
            <h3>Quickstart</h3>
            <p>Canonize → hash → sign → verify → bundle.</p>
            <div class="docCard__meta">5 minutes</div>
          </a>

          <a class="docCard" href="#spec" data-tags="spec formats doc.usd instabyte instafiche raildoc">
            <h3>Formats & Spec</h3>
            <p>DOC.USD, proof bundle schema, custody events, invariants.</p>
            <div class="docCard__meta">Reference</div>
          </a>

          <a class="docCard" href="#verification" data-tags="verification sha256 ed25519 canonical json">
            <h3>Verification</h3>
            <p>How to validate hashes, signatures, and bundle integrity.</p>
            <div class="docCard__meta">Security</div>
          </a>

          <a class="docCard" href="#transport" data-tags="transport custody raildoc movement receipts">
            <h3>Transport & Custody</h3>
            <p>Receipts, idempotency, audit trails, movement protocol.</p>
            <div class="docCard__meta">Operations</div>
          </a>

          <a class="docCard" href="#anchoring" data-tags="onchain anchor evm base timestamp">
            <h3>Onchain Anchoring</h3>
            <p>Optional hash anchoring patterns for public attestation.</p>
            <div class="docCard__meta">Optional</div>
          </a>

          <a class="docCard" href="#sandbox" data-tags="sandbox regulator south carolina compliance pilot">
            <h3>Sandbox Packet</h3>
            <p>What to submit: overview, scope, protections, timeline.</p>
            <div class="docCard__meta">Regulatory</div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section--alt" id="quickstart">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Quickstart</h2>
        <p class="muted">Replace commands with your actual toolchain. This page is a blueprint.</p>

        <div class="grid2">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>1) Canonicalize</h3>
            <pre><code>input:  invoice.json
output: invoice.canonical.json</code></pre>
            <p>Canonical JSON creates stable bytes for hashing and signing.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>2) Hash</h3>
            <pre><code>sha256(invoice.canonical.json) → root</code></pre>
            <p>The root hash is the integrity anchor for the document.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>3) Sign</h3>
            <pre><code>ed25519_sign(root or canonical_bytes) → signature</code></pre>
            <p>Sign the canonical bytes (recommended) to bind semantics to the signature.</p>
          </div>

          <div class="card">
            <h3>4) Bundle</h3>
            <pre><code>bundle = { doc, root, signatures[], metadata }</code></pre>
            <p>Bundle is portable proof: verify anywhere, anytime.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="tip">
          <strong>Tip:</strong> Keep a single “source of truth” for canonicalization rules. Changes must version-bump the spec.
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="spec">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Formats & Spec</h2>
        <div class="grid2">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>DOC.USD (Instrument)</h3>
            <ul class="bullets">
              <li>issuer identity + key fingerprint</li>
              <li>document body (invoice/receipt fields)</li>
              <li>canonicalization version</li>
              <li>root hash</li>
              <li>signature set</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Proof Bundle</h3>
            <ul class="bullets">
              <li>canonical document bytes / pointer</li>
              <li>root hash (sha256)</li>
              <li>signatures (ed25519)</li>
              <li>receipts + custody events (optional)</li>
              <li>chain anchor references (optional)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section--alt" id="verification">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Verification</h2>
        <div class="card card--code">
          <pre><code>Verify(bundle):
  1) canonicalize(doc) → bytes
  2) sha256(bytes) == bundle.root
  3) for each signature:
       ed25519_verify(pubkey, bytes, signature) == true
  4) if chain_anchor present:
       confirm anchor references bundle.root
  5) if custody events present:
       validate ordering + idempotency invariants</code></pre>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="transport">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Transport & Custody</h2>
        <div class="grid2">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Receipt model</h3>
            <p>Every movement produces a receipt referencing the root hash and a custody event id.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>Idempotency</h3>
            <p>All writes should be idempotent by event id to support retries and replays.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section section--alt" id="anchoring">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Onchain Anchoring (Optional)</h2>
        <p class="lead2">Anchor the root hash on an EVM chain for timestamped attestation without exposing document contents.</p>
        <div class="grid2">
          <div class="card">
            <h3>What goes onchain</h3>
            <ul class="bullets">
              <li>root hash (32 bytes)</li>
              <li>timestamp / block reference</li>
              <li>optional issuer id</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="card">
            <h3>What stays offchain</h3>
            <ul class="bullets">
              <li>document content</li>
              <li>PII / sensitive data</li>
              <li>full custody logs (optional)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section" id="sandbox">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Sandbox Packet</h2>
        <div class="callout">
          <div class="callout__copy">
            <p>
              This section is designed to be copy/pasted into a submission. Keep scope small:
              limited participants, limited doc types, and clear disclosures.
            </p>
            <ul class="bullets">
              <li>Problem statement + public benefit</li>
              <li>System overview + verification model</li>
              <li>Pilot scope, participants, timeline</li>
              <li>Consumer protections + risk mitigations</li>
              <li>Exit plan + reporting</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
          <div class="callout__cta">
            <a class="btn btn--primary" href="./index.html#contact">Generate submission email</a>
            <a class="btn btn--ghost" href="./developers.html#recipes">Verification recipes</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer class="footer">
    <div class="container footer__grid">
      <div>
        <div class="footer__brand">TransitCloud</div>
        <div class="footer__sub">Docs Index — Developer Edition</div>
      </div>
      <div class="footer__links">
        <a href="./index.html">Home</a>
        <a href="./developers.html">Developers</a>
      </div>
      <div class="footer__meta">
        <div>© <span id="year"></span> Kam Swygert</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script src="./app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
